---
import AcademyLayout from '../../layouts/AcademyLayout.astro';
---

<AcademyLayout
  title="Summer 2026 Program Series — Nguyen AI Edu"
  description="Summer 2026 series of learning, work, part-time and startup support programs for students and young people."
  activeNav="home"
>
  <section class="academy-container py-12 max-w-4xl">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-academy-text mb-4">
        Summer 2026 learning, work, part-time and startup support program series by Nguyen AI Edu
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-academy-muted">
        For students, young people and those who want to open a new direction
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-academy">
      <p>
        In summer 2026, Nguyen AI Edu opens a series of learning, practice, career orientation, part-time support and startup support programs for students about to graduate, recent graduates, young people looking for new opportunities and those who want to learn more to change careers.
      </p>

      <p>
        The program is organized online nationwide and has in-person activities in Da Lat, Lam Dong province when conditions allow.
      </p>

      <p>
        Nguyen AI Edu prioritizes those who carry the Nguyen surname, but the program remains open to suitable young people who have a spirit of real learning, real doing, love artificial intelligence, technology, creativity, startups and want to create real value for themselves, their families, their local communities and society.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Why this program was built</h2>

      <p>
        Many students about to graduate or already graduated face the same problem:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Studied a lot but do not know where to start.</li>
        <li>Have a degree but lack a real capability portfolio.</li>
        <li>Want to work but have no experience.</li>
        <li>Want part-time work but do not know which job to choose to both earn income and develop skills.</li>
        <li>Want to start a business but have no direction, do not know how to build a product, brand, customers and operating model.</li>
        <li>Want to use artificial intelligence but do not know how to use it correctly, usefully and to produce real results.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Nguyen AI Edu was built to support exactly that group of people.
      </p>

      <p>
        We do not see learning as just listening to lectures. Learning must come with practice. Practice must come with a product. A product must have evidence. Evidence must help the learner open up opportunities for employment, part-time work, startups or developing a new career path.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Who the program is for</h2>

      <p>The program is suitable for:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>final-year students;</li>
        <li>recent graduates;</li>
        <li>young people looking for work;</li>
        <li>people who want part-time work in the summer;</li>
        <li>people who want to change career direction;</li>
        <li>people who want to learn more about artificial intelligence;</li>
        <li>people who want to build a personal brand;</li>
        <li>people who want to start a small business;</li>
        <li>people who want to join technology, education, media, business or community projects;</li>
        <li>people who love Da Lat, Lam Dong and want to join in-person experiences when scheduled;</li>
        <li>people who carry the Nguyen surname and want to contribute to a learning, working and startup ecosystem with character.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        <strong>Priority age range:</strong> 20 to 49, especially students, new workers and young people looking for career change opportunities.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Focus areas</h2>

      <p>
        The summer 2026 program series by Nguyen AI Edu focuses on the following content groups:
      </p>

      <h3>1. Artificial intelligence for learning and work</h3>

      <p>
        Learners are guided on how to use artificial intelligence to learn faster, research better, write better, plan better and handle work more clearly.
      </p>

      <p>
        The goal is not to use tools for fun, but to know how to use artificial intelligence to produce verifiable results.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Capability portfolio and job search</h3>

      <p>
        Learners are supported in building a personal profile, positioning their capabilities, describing experience, preparing sample products and presenting capabilities in a way that employers, partners or customers can understand.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Part-time work and project-based internships</h3>

      <p>
        The program guides learners toward part-time jobs with long-term development value, such as content support, media, research, community care, project assistance, learning operations, business support, verified data entry and jobs that can be done online.
      </p>

      <h3>4. Content creation and personal brand building</h3>

      <p>
        Learners are guided on how to build a personal voice, content topics, posting schedule, career story and how to use content to open up learning, work, collaboration or startup opportunities.
      </p>

      <h3>5. Local brand and national brand building</h3>

      <p>
        The program prioritizes ideas tied to local communities, native products, culture, tourism, agriculture, education, community and Vietnamese values that can be developed into sustainable brands.
      </p>

      <h3>6. Small startups and digital business</h3>

      <p>
        Learners are introduced to startup thinking from the basics: identify a problem, understand customers, design a product, test the market, build a landing page, create content, set prices, sell on a trial basis and improve.
      </p>

      <h3>7. Investment, scholarship sponsorship and development opportunities</h3>

      <p>
        Learners are introduced to foundational knowledge about investment, sponsorship, fundraising, scholarships, responsibility to sponsors and how to present a valuable idea. This content is educational and orientational, not a financial investment invitation and does not promise returns.
      </p>

      <h3>8. Freedom and self-determination in work</h3>

      <p>
        The ultimate goal is to help learners gradually build the ability to self-learn, self-do, self-build a portfolio, self-create products, self-find opportunities and self-take responsibility for their own career path.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Learning format</h2>

      <h3>Online nationwide</h3>

      <p>
        Learners can join from any province or city. Online learning content suits students on summer break, recent graduates, working people or those who want to learn more outside working hours.
      </p>

      <h3>In-person experience in Da Lat, Lam Dong</h3>

      <p>
        When conditions allow, Nguyen AI Edu will open in-person activities in Da Lat, Lam Dong province. This is an opportunity for learners to meet experts, work in teams, join real projects, practice presentation skills and build products in a creative environment.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>July 2026 scholarships</h2>

      <p>
        In July 2026, Nguyen AI Edu plans to prioritize the first 11 scholarships for each program group.
      </p>

      <p>
        Scholarships are for early registrants with clear goals, a serious learning spirit and readiness to produce a real product after the learning process.
      </p>

      <p><strong>Priority for:</strong></p>

      <ul>
        <li>people who carry the Nguyen surname;</li>
        <li>students about to graduate;</li>
        <li>recent graduates;</li>
        <li>young people looking for work;</li>
        <li>people in circumstances that need support;</li>
        <li>people who love artificial intelligence and startups;</li>
        <li>people who want to develop a local brand, community or personal project;</li>
        <li>people who commit to completing lessons, tests, practice and a final product.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        After the 11 scholarships in July 2026 are filled, learners can choose:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>free programs if still open;</li>
        <li>partially supported programs;</li>
        <li>paid courses on edu.nguyenai.net;</li>
        <li>more in-depth programs when conditions allow.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Early registrants will be prioritized for review first.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Important clarifications</h2>

      <div class="p-4 bg-yellow-50 rounded-lg border border-yellow-200 my-6">
        <p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-2">Nguyen AI Edu does not promise:</p>
        <ul class="text-yellow-700">
          <li>Guaranteed employment</li>
          <li>Guaranteed fundraising</li>
          <li>Guaranteed startup success</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p>
        What the program commits to within its ability is to create a learning, practice, orientation, feedback and support environment so that learners have the opportunity to build real capability.
      </p>

      <p>
        Learners who want to go far need to take responsibility for themselves: study fully, do the work, correct mistakes, practice, create products, submit evidence and complete their capability portfolio.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>What learners should have after the program</h2>

      <p>
        Depending on the learning group, learners will be oriented to produce one or more of the following results:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>a personal capability portfolio;</li>
        <li>a career plan;</li>
        <li>content products;</li>
        <li>a personal or project landing page;</li>
        <li>a clearly presented startup idea;</li>
        <li>a job search or part-time work plan;</li>
        <li>a small verifiable project;</li>
        <li>a better application portfolio;</li>
        <li>the ability to use artificial intelligence in learning and work;</li>
        <li>direction for building a personal brand, local brand or community brand.</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Who should register early</h2>

      <p>You should register early if you:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>are about to graduate;</li>
        <li>just graduated but are not clear on your direction;</li>
        <li>want to learn more in summer 2026;</li>
        <li>want part-time work but do not want only short-term jobs that do not develop skills;</li>
        <li>want to use artificial intelligence in learning, work and creativity;</li>
        <li>want to build a personal brand;</li>
        <li>want to start a small business;</li>
        <li>want to join a community of learners and doers with direction;</li>
        <li>want a chance to receive a scholarship before spots run out.</li>
      </ul>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <h2>Register</h2>

      <p>
        Register and follow information at:
      </p>

      <div class="my-6 p-6 bg-academy-header rounded-lg border border-academy-border">
        <a href="/en/apply" class="academy-btn academy-btn-primary text-lg">
          Register now at edu.nguyenai.net
        </a>
      </div>

      <p>
        July 2026 prioritizes early registrants.<br />
        Priority for those who carry the Nguyen surname, but still open to suitable, serious people who want to create real value.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-8 text-lg text-academy-accent font-semibold">
        Nguyen AI Edu welcomes young people who want to learn for real, do for real, create real products and open up a new direction for their future.
      </p>

      <hr class="my-8 border-academy-border" />

      <div class="p-4 bg-academy-header rounded-lg border border-academy-border">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-academy-text mb-3">Support contact</h3>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm">
          <span class="text-academy-accent" aria-hidden="true">&#128241;</span>
          <span>Hotline/Zalo: <a href="tel:0989660750" class="text-academy-accent font-medium hover:underline">0989660750</a></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</AcademyLayout>
